On June 24, 2022, the President signed three bills into law that designate certain United States Postal Service facilities as post office buildings named after notable individuals. The first bill, H.R. 735, designates the facility located at 502 East Cotati Avenue in Cotati, California, as the Arturo L. Ibleto Post Office Building. Representative Mike Thompson and others were thanked for their leadership in this endeavor. The second bill, H.R. 767, designates the facility located at 40 Fulton Street in Middletown, New York, as the Benjamin A. Gilman Post Office Building. Representative Sean Patrick Maloney and others were acknowledged for their leadership. Lastly, H.R. 1444 designates the facility located at 132 North Loudoun Street, Suite 1 in Winchester, Virginia, as the Patsy Cline Post Office. Representative Wexton and the bipartisan efforts of the Virginia delegation were recognized for their leadership in this initiative.